   - The RGB path has nested loops (h × w × step) which is computationally intensive
   - The planar path has similar nested loops (planes × h × w)
   - Memory access patterns are sequential which is good for cache efficiency
   - The LUT lookups are already using precomputed tables

2. **Optimization Opportunities**:
   - The inner loops can be unrolled for better pipelining
   - The RGB path can be optimized by removing the inner k-loop when step size is known
   - The planar path can benefit from loop unrolling as well
   - We can use pointer arithmetic more efficiently

3. **Selected Optimization**:
   - The highest impact optimization would be to unroll the RGB path inner loop when step=3 or step=4 (common cases for RGB/BGR formats)
   - This eliminates the innermost loop counter and conditional checks
   - The optimization maintains the exact same behavior but with fewer instructions

